become boring for three years.

48
00:03:38,020 --> 00:03:39,350
I guess you're right.

49
00:03:51,300 --> 00:03:53,310
Just as I thought,
it started to rain again.

50
00:03:54,010 --> 00:03:56,400
The rainy season will be over soon.

51
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:57,170
Right.

52
00:04:19,160 --> 00:04:19,930
Oh ?

53
00:04:22,990 --> 00:04:24,700
Kunimi !

54
00:04:28,130 --> 00:04:28,880
Hi.

55
00:04:33,970 --> 00:04:35,900
You run every day ?

56
00:04:35,900 --> 00:04:40,130
Yeah. It's been a habit
of mine for a long time.

57
00:04:40,130 --> 00:04:44,270
Besides, leg strength is important for every sport, not just baseball.

58
00:04:45,930 --> 00:04:48,940
Regardless of what I end up doing, it won't be meaningless.

59
00:04:51,170 --> 00:04:54,600
If you haven't decided what you're going to do yet...

60
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:57,530
...can you temporarily be the
coach for the Baseball Fan Club ?

61
00:04:57,530 --> 00:04:58,450
Hm ?

62
00:04:58,450 --> 00:05:02,250
If you're just coaching, you
don't have to tax your elbow.

63
00:05:06,650 --> 00:05:09,500
You don't have to do it,
unless you have free time.

64
00:05:10,620 --> 00:05:15,650
I'm not good at telling people what to do.

65
00:05:19,200 --> 00:05:21,380
Oh, I know.

66
00:05:21,380 --> 00:05:24,350
If you're going to get someone
to coach, Noda would be better.

67
00:05:24,350 --> 00:05:25,740
Noda ?

68
00:05:25,740 --> 00:05:26,550
Yeah.

69
00:05:27,760 --> 00:05:32,100
From pitch-calling to defensive
alignment, the flow of the game.

70
00:05:32,100 --> 00:05:35,920
Catchers always have to keep an eye on all aspects of the game.

71
