Temperamentally, too, he's better suited for the role than a selfish pitcher.

72
00:05:42,750 --> 00:05:43,670
Kunimi.



73
00:05:43,670 --> 00:05:44,550
Hm ?

74
00:05:44,550 --> 00:05:47,110
You don't play any 
position other than pitcher ?

75
00:05:48,780 --> 00:05:51,440
Thanks to my selfish personality.

76
00:05:51,440 --> 00:05:53,000
Anyway, Noda is the best.

77
00:05:54,360 --> 00:05:56,150
Then, I'll ask.

78
00:06:00,840 --> 00:06:02,380
He finally caught up to me.

79
00:06:05,760 --> 00:06:07,210
Hey...Hiro...!

80
00:06:07,840 --> 00:06:11,650
You should slow down. 
Are you trying to kill me ?

81
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:14,000
Good morning.

82
00:06:16,510 --> 00:06:22,250
Hoo...hoo...hoo...

83
00:06:22,250 --> 00:06:24,200
Are you an owl or something ?

84
00:06:24,200 --> 00:06:27,190
What is your relationship to Hiro ?

85
00:06:27,190 --> 00:06:32,500
We attend the same school. 
We only recently met, and that's it.

86
00:06:34,700 --> 00:06:36,510
That's good.

87
00:06:36,510 --> 00:06:39,960
This guy is a pervert, so you
shouldn't get involved with him.

88
00:06:39,960 --> 00:06:40,900
Hey...

89
00:06:43,230 --> 00:06:47,000
In that respect, as much of a pervert as I am, I'm older and have more self-restraint.


90
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:51,250
So girls are much safer with me.

91
00:06:51,250 --> 00:06:52,000
Huh ?

92
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:56,050
Moreover, this guy has a monthly allowance of just 5000 yen.

93
00:06:56,050 --> 00:06:57,450
But as for me, look.

94
00:06:58,700 --> 00:07:00,200
As you can see, I have cards...

95
00:07:00,200 --> 00:07:03,710
...and a secret savings account that my wife doesn't know about, so I live quite comfortably.

96
00:07:03,710 --> 00:07:04,710
Hey...

97
00:07:05,160 --> 00:07:08,510
Would you like to have
dinner with me sometime ?

98
00:07:08,980 --> 00:07:13,470
Well, the company's entertainment expenses will pay for it, so you shouldn't feel shy.

99
00:07:14,100 --> 00:07:14,450
...

100
00:07:16,290 --> 00:07:20,050
You can learn a lot by 
going out with an older guy.

101
00:07:20,050 --> 00:07:21,790
Let's see...

102
00:07:21,790 --> 00:07:23,110
Oh, I'm Koga.

103
00:07:23,110 --> 00:07:25,060
Yes, Ms. Koga.

104
00:07:25,060 --> 00:07:26,370
Well, I'll think about it.

105
00:07:28,310 --> 00:07:30,300
You can fire him.

106
00:07:30,300 --> 00:07:31,250
...?

107
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:38,510
I have to go. I need
to get to school early.

108
00:07:38,510 --> 00:07:39,590
Hm ?

109
00:07:39,590 --> 00:07:43,360
I'm going to put up some posters to
recruit new members for the Fan Club.

110
00:07:43,360 --> 00:07:46,690
Someone has been tearing them
down no matter how many I put up.

111
00:07:46,690 --> 00:07:47,430
I see.

112
00:07:52,470 --> 00:07:54,970
Good luck. 
Bye, Ms. Koga.

113
00:07:55,870 --> 00:07:58,290
Huh ? Ms. Koga...?

114
00:07:59,510 --> 00:08:02,290
You should look forward to 
getting called in by your boss.

115
00:08:02,290 --> 00:08:03,470
What ?

116
00:08:04,100 --> 00:08:07,000
President Koga's daughter...?

117
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:10,300
If you're transferred to a post in some other city, you should go there alone.

118
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:16,110
It's torn down again.

119
00:08:18,850 --> 00:08:20,270
I'm not going to back down.


120
00:08:20,980 --> 00:08:23,220
Haruka, I'm done here.

121
00:08:24,370 --> 00:08:27,170
Oh, thanks, Asako.
I appreciate it.

122
00:08:27,690 --> 00:08:30,480
But it's probably useless.

123
00:08:30,730 --> 00:08:35,700
You're the hero !

124
00:08:30,730 --> 00:08:35,700
The hot
springtime
of youth

125
00:08:30,730 --> 00:08:35,700
Now play ball !

126
00:08:30,730 --> 00:08:35,700
Hot-blooded

127
00:08:30,730 --> 00:08:35,700
Baseball Fan Club
is Looking For
 New Members !

128
00:08:31,650 --> 00:08:35,700
Baseball is an old people's game. No one's interested.

129
00:08:36,830 --> 00:08:40,010
Then I like old men ?

130
00:08:40,010 --> 00:08:41,060
You like old men ?

131
00:08:42,090 --> 00:08:44,200
You didn't fall for
my father, did you ?

132
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:46,150
What ? What're you talking about ?

133
00:08:46,150 --> 00:08:47,600
Oh, that's not what
 I'm talking about.

134
00:08:50,150 --> 00:08:53,380
Oh, that's right. 
Show your best stuff, old man.

135
00:08:54,390 --> 00:08:55,620
What was that ?

136
00:08:55,620 --> 00:08:57,040
Um, Noda.

137
00:08:57,340 --> 00:08:58,410
Yeah ?

138
00:08:58,410 --> 00:09:02,150
I have something I want to ask you.

139
00:09:02,150 --> 00:09:04,550
Can you spare some 
time for me after school ?

140
00:09:05,270 --> 00:09:06,400
W...what ?

141
00:09:07,360 --> 00:09:08,550
What...?

142
00:09:08,550 --> 00:09:10,440
No way...
I can't believe it.

143
00:09:14,610 --> 00:09:16,500
Hey, hey ! Come on !

144
00:09:16,050 --> 00:09:16,330
...!

145
00:09:16,330 --> 00:09:16,560


146
00:09:35,330 --> 00:09:36,020
Hey, Maruyama.

147
00:09:38,880 --> 00:09:40,250
My elbow...

148
00:09:41,550 --> 00:09:43,080
Hello ? Hello ?

149
00:09:44,050 --> 00:09:45,510
What's wrong, Tachibana ?

150
00:09:45,510 --> 00:09:47,420
No one's here.

151
00:09:46,800 --> 00:09:51,700
Uetake Clinic

152
00:09:47,420 --> 00:09:49,850
The windows are closed 
and the curtains are closed.

153
00:09:49,850 --> 00:09:51,440
They're not supposed
to be closed today.

154
00:09:52,310 --> 00:09:54,500
It can't be helped. Let's have him examined at another hospital.

155
00:09:58,780 --> 00:09:59,830
Goal !

156
00:10:01,210 --> 00:10:03,660
An amazing talent, Kine
has a gold medal right leg.

157
00:10:04,700 --> 00:10:05,600
Huh ? They're...?

158
00:10:08,850 --> 00:10:10,030
Why are those two...?

159
00:10:11,020 --> 00:10:12,300
Hey, Peeping Tom.

160
00:10:13,640 --> 00:10:14,650
Don't scare me.

161
00:10:15,860 --> 00:10:18,650
Just as I thought, 
you're feeling uneasy.

162
00:10:18,650 --> 00:10:20,450
What are you talking about ?

163
00:10:20,450 --> 00:10:25,960
Those two have been bonding since the baseball game the other day.

164
00:10:25,960 --> 00:10:28,320
It can't be true ! There's no way Koga would go out with a guy like him !

165
00:10:28,320 --> 00:10:29,720
Oh, they disappeared.

166
00:10:31,030 --> 00:10:31,780
Where are they ?

167
00:10:32,010 --> 00:10:35,450
Women's Dressing Room

168
00:10:32,910 --> 00:10:36,340
Probably the unoccupied dressing room of the girls' swimming club.

169
00:10:36,340 --> 00:10:38,000
How do you know ?


170
00:10:38,740 --> 00:10:40,510
Noda is good at it.

171
00:10:40,510 --> 00:10:43,860
Taking a girl into the
dressing room, I mean.

172
00:10:44,150 --> 00:10:45,730
W...what ?!



173
00:10:48,450 --> 00:10:49,600
Get out !

174
00:10:50,320 --> 00:10:52,980
So can I really ask you to do it ?

175
00:10:55,760 --> 00:10:58,810
Yeah. As you can see, 
my rehab is going well.

176
00:10:58,810 --> 00:11:02,800
More importantly, there's no way I can turn down your request.

177
00:11:02,800 --> 00:11:07,550
But I had never heard that butterfly-style swimming is good for rehabbing a bad back.

178
00:11:07,550 --> 00:11:09,640
That's what the doctor says, 
so it must be true.

179
00:11:10,470 --> 00:11:14,370
I have to be able to
hit some fungo at least.

180
00:11:14,370 --> 00:11:15,740
Okay, I've got to do one more lap.

181
00:11:29,160 --> 00:11:30,130
Don't call me.

182
00:11:39,950 --> 00:11:40,460
eyecatch

183
00:11:57,290 --> 00:11:59,450
Maruyama hurt his elbow ?

184
00:11:59,950 --> 00:12:04,820
Yeah. Right before the preliminary, we lost our ace pitcher.

185
00:12:04,820 --> 00:12:09,890
But didn't you say that Maruyama's sore elbow was just fatigue ?



186
00:12:10,450 --> 00:12:13,450
That's what that doctor
named Uetake said.

187
00:12:13,450 --> 00:12:17,700
But it turned out differently when they had him examined at the University Hospital.

188
00:12:17,700 --> 00:12:23,200
Dr. Uetake is famous around 
here for sports medicine, right ?

189
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:23,790
Yeah.

190
00:12:37,170 --> 00:12:38,400
607...

191
00:12:39,090 --> 00:12:42,650
Hey, Hiro. Can you 
get me some beer ?

192
00:12:44,040 --> 00:12:46,370
Sent Onono Imoko to Sui.

193
00:12:47,160 --> 00:12:50,970
608...

194
00:12:50,970 --> 00:12:54,660
Emissaries to Sui return
to Japan via Kudara.

195
00:12:54,660 --> 00:12:56,650
Honey, this is strange !

196
00:12:56,650 --> 00:12:59,870
Hiro is studying.
It's going to rain hard.

197
00:13:01,250 --> 00:13:02,860
What's wrong with him ?

198
00:13:02,860 --> 00:13:04,450
Just let me kill time however I like.

199
00:13:17,450 --> 00:13:20,900
First-Year
Mid-Term
Top 50 Scorers

200
00:13:19,020 --> 00:13:22,610
They should stop doing this sort of thing in this day and age.

201
00:13:22,610 --> 00:13:26,990
But for those who worked hard, it will 
be kind of a reward, don't you think ?

202
00:13:26,990 --> 00:13:29,360
So who worked hard ?

203
00:13:29,360 --> 00:13:34,240
You got into the top 50 just because you guessed right. Don't get too carried away.

204
00:13:36,450 --> 00:13:38,150
You have to narrow 
down the target pitch.

205
00:13:38,150 --> 00:13:41,550
If you swing at everything, you
 won't be able to hit for average.

